                                <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name=3D"content"=
 -->
                <p>Divide two numbers, a dividend and a divisor, and find t=
he answer as a quotient with a remainder. Learn how to solve long division =
with remainders, or practice your own long division problems and use this c=
alculator to check your answers.</p>
                <p>Long division with remainders is one of two methods of d=
oing long division by hand. It is a little easier than solving a division p=
roblem by finding a quotient answer with a decimal. If you need to do long =
division with decimals use our
                    <a href=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/calculators/m=
ath/longdivisiondecimals.php">Long Division with Decimals Calculator</a>.
                </p>
                <h2>What Are the Parts of Division</h2>
                <p>For the division sentence 487 =C3=B7 32 =3D 15 R 7</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>487 is the dividend</li>
                    <li>32 is the divisor</li>
                    <li>15 is the quotient part of the answer</li>
                    <li>7 is the remainder part of the answer</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    <img src=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/images/longd=
ivision/divisionparts.png" width=3D"200" height=3D"220" alt=3D"solve a long=
 division problem with parts of division: dividend, divisor, quotient, rema=
inder" title=3D"Parts of long division: dividend, divisor, quotient, remain=
der">
                </p>
                <div class=3D"clearBoth"></div>
                <h2>How to do Long Division With Remainders</h2>
                <p>From the example above let's divide 487 by 32 showing th=
e work.</p>
                <div class=3D"table ExampleTable centered">
                    <div class=3D"row">
                        <div class=3D"cell headerCell"><strong>Long Divisio=
n</strong></div>
                        <div class=3D"cell headerCell"><strong>Step-by-Step=
</strong></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class=3D"row">
                        <div class=3D"cell">
                            <img src=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/imag=
es/longdivision/step01.png" alt=3D"set up the problem long division 487 div=
ided by 32" width=3D"118" height=3D"80">
                        </div>
                        <div class=3D"cell">Set up the division problem wit=
h the long division symbol or the long division bracket.
                            <br>
                            <br>
                                          Put 487, the dividend, on the ins=
ide of the bracket. The dividend is the number you're dividing.
                            <br>
                                          Put 32, the divisor, on the outsi=
de of the bracket. The divisor is the number you're dividing by.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class=3D"row">
                        <div class=3D"cell">
                            <img src=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/imag=
es/longdivision/step01.png" alt=3D"step 1 divide dividend by divisor in lon=
g division 487 divided by 32" width=3D"118" height=3D"80">
                        </div>
                        <div class=3D"cell">Divide the first number of the =
dividend, 4 by the divisor, 32.
                            <br>
                            <br>
                                          4 divided by 32 is 0, with a rema=
inder of 4. You can ignore the remainder for now.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class=3D"row">
                        <div class=3D"cell">
                            <img src=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/imag=
es/longdivision/step02.png" alt=3D"step 2 subtraction in long division prob=
lem 487 divided by 32" width=3D"118" height=3D"155">
                        </div>
                        <div class=3D"cell">Put the 0 on top of the divisio=
n bracket.
                            <br>
                                          This is the beginning of the quot=
ient answer.
                            <br>
                            <br>
                                          Next, multiply 0 by the divisor 3=
2 and insert the result 0 below the first number of the dividend inside the=
 bracket.
                            <br>
                            <br>
                                          0 * 32 =3D 0
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class=3D"row">
                        <div class=3D"cell">
                            <img src=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/imag=
es/longdivision/step03.png" alt=3D"step 3 long division 487 divided by 32" =
width=3D"118" height=3D"155">
                        </div>
                        <div class=3D"cell">Draw a line under the 0 and sub=
tract 0 from 4.
                            <br>
                            <br>
                                          4 - 0 =3D 4
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class=3D"row">
                        <div class=3D"cell">
                            <img src=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/imag=
es/longdivision/step04.png" alt=3D"step 4 long division 487 divided by 32" =
width=3D"118" height=3D"155">
                        </div>
                        <div class=3D"cell">Bring down the next number of t=
he dividend and insert it after the 4 so you have 48.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class=3D"row">
                        <div class=3D"cell">
                            <img src=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/imag=
es/longdivision/step05.png" alt=3D"step 5 long division 487 divided by 32" =
width=3D"118" height=3D"155">
                        </div>
                        <div class=3D"cell">Divide 48 by the divisor, 32. T=
he answer is 1. You can ignore the remainder for now.
                            <br>
                            <br>
                                          48 =C3=B7 32 =3D 1
                            <br>
                            <br>
                                          Note that you could skip all of t=
he previous steps with zeros and jump straight to this step. You just need =
to realize how many digits in the dividend you need to skip over to get you=
r first non-zero value in the quotient answer. In this case you could divid=
e 32 into 48 straight away.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class=3D"row">
                        <div class=3D"cell">
                            <img src=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/imag=
es/longdivision/step06.png" alt=3D"step 6 long division 487 divided by 32" =
width=3D"118" height=3D"197">
                        </div>
                        <div class=3D"cell">Put the 1 on top of the divisio=
n bar, to the right of the 0. Next, multiply 1 by 32 and write the answer u=
nder 48.
                            <br>
                            <br>
                                          1 * 32 =3D 32
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class=3D"row">
                        <div class=3D"cell">
                            <img src=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/imag=
es/longdivision/step07.png" alt=3D"step 7 long division 487 divided by 32" =
width=3D"118" height=3D"215">
                        </div>
                        <div class=3D"cell">Draw a line and subtract 32 fro=
m 48.
                            <br>
                            <br>
                                          48 - 32 =3D 16
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class=3D"row">
                        <div class=3D"cell">
                            <img src=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/imag=
es/longdivision/step08.png" alt=3D"step 8 long division 487 divided by 32" =
width=3D"118" height=3D"215">
                        </div>
                        <div class=3D"cell">Bring down the next number from=
 the dividend and insert it after the 16 so you have 167.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class=3D"row">
                        <div class=3D"cell">
                            <img src=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/imag=
es/longdivision/step09.png" alt=3D"step 9 long division 487 divided by 32" =
width=3D"118" height=3D"215">
                        </div>
                        <div class=3D"cell">Divide 167 by the 32. See a pat=
tern emerging?
                            <br>
                            <br>
                                          167 =C3=B7 32 is 5 with a remaind=
er of 7
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class=3D"row">
                        <div class=3D"cell">
                            <img src=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/imag=
es/longdivision/step10.png" alt=3D"step 10 long division 487 divided by 32"=
 width=3D"118" height=3D"264">
                        </div>
                        <div class=3D"cell">Put the 5 on top of the divisio=
n bar, to the right of the 1. Multiply 5 by 32 and write the answer under 1=
67.
                            <br>
                            <br>
                                          5 * 32 =3D 160
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class=3D"row">
                        <div class=3D"cell">
                            <img src=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/imag=
es/longdivision/step11.png" alt=3D"step 11 long division 487 divided by 32"=
 width=3D"118" height=3D"296">
                        </div>
                        <div class=3D"cell">Draw a line and subtract 160 fr=
om 167.
                            <br>
                            <br>
                                          167 - 160 =3D 7
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class=3D"row">
                        <div class=3D"cell">
                            <img src=3D"https://www.calculatorsoup.com/imag=
es/longdivision/step11.png" alt=3D"step 11 long division 487 divided by 32"=
 width=3D"118" height=3D"296">
                        </div>
                        <div class=3D"cell">Since 7 is less than 32 your lo=
ng division is done. You have your answer: The quotient is 15 and the remai=
nder is 7.
                            <br>
                            <br>
                                          So, 487 =C3=B7 32 =3D 15 with a r=
emainder of 7
                            <br>
                            <br>
                                          For longer dividends, you would c=
ontinue repeating the division and multiplication steps until you bring dow=
n every digit from the divdend and solve the long division.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p></p>
